🌸 Happy AAPI Heritage Month! 🌸

Let's celebrate the incredible contributions of Sung Yeon Choimorrow, Dr. Anu Kumar, and Miriam Yeung, who are making a remarkable difference in the world of women's rights and reproductive health. 🌏

🙌 Sung Yeon Choimorrow, as the Executive Director of @NAPAWF, fearlessly advocates for the rights of Asian American and Pacific Islander women. Her commitment to gender equality and challenging stereotypes inspires us all! 💪✊

🌟 Dr. Anu Kumar, President and CEO of @IpasOrg, dedicates her expertise to expanding access to safe abortion and contraceptive care worldwide. Her tireless efforts empower women to make informed choices about their reproductive health. 🌏🩺

💥 Miriam Yeung, the former Executive Director of @NAPAWF, is a champion for the rights and well-being of Asian American and Pacific Islander women. Her leadership has inspired us to dismantle barriers and create a more equitable society. 🌸🤝

🌏🌟 Let's take a moment to recognize their exceptional advocacy, leadership, and intersectional approach to addressing gender inequalities. Their work paves the way for a more inclusive and just world. Together, we can amplify their voices and support their impactful initiatives. 💕

🌟 What is BMI and why is it important?

🔍 BMI stands for Body Mass Index. It's not perfect, but it's a simple calculation that helps assess whether your weight is within a healthy range based on your height. It's an important tool that healthcare professionals use to understand your overall health.

📏 How is BMI calculated? Well, here's the formula: BMI = weight (kg) / square of height (m²). 

⚖️ Why is BMI important? Your BMI provides a general indication of whether you're underweight, normal weight, overweight, or obese. It helps you and your healthcare provider understand any potential health risks associated with your weight.

💪🏼 If you're a woman with a higher BMI, estrogen-containing birth control pills might not be the best fit for you.

Your feelings are valid, and your health journey is uniquely yours. It's time we prioritize our own needs. Here are a few reminders to keep in mind during your next appointment. 💖

📝 PREPARE A LIST: Jot down your questions and symptoms before your appointment. Having them on hand ensures you won't forget anything crucial during the visit.

👂 TRUST YOUR INSTINCTS: If something doesn't feel right, don't be afraid to seek a second opinion or call your HCP right away.

💃 BE YOUR OWN ADVOCATE: Educate yourself about your health conditions and treatment options. Knowledge is empowering, and it gives you a stronger voice in your healthcare decisions.

💖 SELF-LOVE & COMPASSION: Be kind to yourself, especially when navigating health challenges. You deserve gentle care and support every step of the way.
